
 Usage

This function calculates the polynomial coefficients for
given roots

      p = poly(r)

when r is a vector, is a vector whose elements are the
coefficients of the polynomial whose roots are the elements
of r. Alternately, you can provide a matrix

      p = poly(A)

when A is an N x N square matrix, is a row vector with N+1
elements which are the coefficients of the characteristic
polynomial, det(lambda*eye(size(A))-A).
